Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharp turn. Clay fine light beige-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Helios head symbol.
Curator's comments: Pencil '369'. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 121, 10. Name Damokles. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0116.19.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0900)
